title.narrative: COMMUNITY BEHAVIOUR CHANGE

description.narrative: Output 3.1: Communities are enabled to practice positive social behaviors in the best interest of the child and to demand the delivery of quality and resilient, child-friendly services., which contributes to Cross Sectoral - Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Prevention Of Harmful Practice, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Girls and boys grow up in resilient, inclusive and child friendly communities, that are supported by enabling environment and systems that provide an equitable chance in life.

description.narrative: UNICEF enhanced youth engagement at community level through capacity building to 150 youth in the five districts in areas of data collection to enhance feedback between the communities and duty bearers, accountability, and COVID-19 information dissemination.; UNICEF supported young people, faith leaders and traditional leaders to work in harmonized ways in ending child marriages thereby reaching 91,534 community members.; Fifty-one faith actors were equipped with skills using digital platforms in disseminating information on COVID-19 thereby reaching over 25,000 people.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:23/12/2021
